<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1971, <em>Poetry, Language, Thought</em>,
Albert Hofstadter (trans.), New York: Harper &amp; Row.</li>

<li>Hobbes, Thomas, <em>Leviathan</em>, Richard Tuck (ed.), Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press, 1996 [1991].</li>

<li>Hume, David, <em>Dialogues Concerning Natural Religion</em>, New
York: Bobbs-Merrill, 1947.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Enquiry Concerning the Principles of
Morals</em>, L. A. Selby-Biggie (ed.), Oxford: Clarendon Press,
1975.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>A Treatise of Human Nature</em>, L. A.
Selby-Bigges (ed.), Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1978.</li>

<li>Hutcheson, F., <em>Essay on the Nature and Conduct of the Passions
with Illustrations on the Moral Sense</em>, A. Garrett (ed.),
Indianapolis: Liberty Fund, 1991.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Inquiry into the Original of our Ideas
of Beauty and Virtue: In Two Treatises</em>, Wolfgang Leidhold (ed.),
Indianapolis: Liberty Fund, 2004.</li>

<li>Kant, Immanuel, <em>Critique of Practical Reason</em>, Mary Gregor
(ed. and trans.), Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1997.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Critique of Pure Reason</em>, Paul
Guyer and Allen W. Wood (eds. and trans.), Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, 1998.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Groundwork of the Metaphysics of
Morals</em>, Mary Gregor (ed. and trans.), Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, 1998.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Prolegomena to any Future
Metaphysics</em>, Gary Hatfield (ed. and trans.), Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, 1997.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Religion within the Boundaries of Mere
Reason</em>, in <em>Religion and Rational Theology</em>, Allen W. Wood
and George di Giovanni (eds.), Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,
1996.</li>

<li>Kierkegaard, S., <em>Samlede Voerker</em>, A. B. Drachmann, J. L.
Heiberg and H. O. Lange (eds.), Copenhagen: Gyldendal,
1901&ndash;06.</li>

<li>Leibniz, G. W., <em>New Essays on Human Understanding</em>, Peter
Remnant and Jonathan Bennett (eds. and trans.), Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, 1996.</li>

<li>Levinas, E., 1969, <em>Totality and Infinity</em>, trans. Alphonso
Lingis, Pittsburgh: Duquesne University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Ethics and Infinity</em>, trans.
Richard A. Cohen, Pittsburgh: Duquesne University Press, 1985.</li>

<li>Locke, John, <em>The Reasonableness of Christianity</em>, I. T.
Ramsey (ed.), Stanford: Stanford University Press, 1958.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Two Treatises on Government</em> and
<em>A Letter Concerning Toleration</em>, Ian Shapiro (ed.), New Haven:
Yale University Press, 2003.</li>

<li>Luther, Martin, <em>The Bondage of the Will,</em> in <em>Martin
Luther: Selections from his Writings</em>, John Dillenberger (ed.),
Garden City: Doubleday, 1961.</li>

<li>Maimonides, <em>The Guide of the Perplexed</em>, trans. Schlomo
Pines, Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 1963.</li>

<li>Marx, Karl, &ldquo;Critique of Hegel&rsquo;s Philosophy of
Right,&rdquo; <em>Early Writings</em>, Rodney Livingstone and Gregor
Benton (trans.), London: Penguin Books, 1992 [1975].</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, &ldquo;Economic and Philosophic
Manuscripts,&rdquo; <em>Early Writings</em>, Rodney Livingstone and
Gregor Benton (trans.), London: Penguin Books, 1992 [1975].</li>

<li>Mill, J. S., <em>Autobiography</em>, Jack Stillinger (ed.),
Boston: Houghton Mifflin Co., 1969.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1874, <em>Three Essays on Religion</em>,
London: Henry Holt.</li>

<li>Moore, G. E., 1903, <em>Principia Ethica</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Nietzsche, Friedrich, <em>The Gay Science</em>, Walter Kaufman
(trans.), New York: Vintage Books, 1974.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>On the Genealogy of Morals</em>, Walter
Kaufman (trans.), New York: Vintage Books, 1967.</li>

<li>Paley, W., 1830, <em>The Principles of Moral and Political
Philosophy</em>, Cambridge: Hillard and Brown.</li>

<li>Plato, <em>Collected Dialogues</em>, Edith Hamilton and Huntington
Cairns (eds.), Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1963.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Republic</em>, Robin Waterfield
(trans.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1993.</li>

<li>Rousseau, J.-J., <em>The Social Contract and other Later Political
Writings</em>, Victor Gourevitch (ed.), Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, 1997.</li>

<li>Russell, B., 1910, &ldquo;The Elements of Ethics,&rdquo;
<em>Philosophical Essays</em>, New York: Longmans, Green.</li>

<li>Sartre, J.-P., 1957, <em>Existentialism and Human Emotions</em>,
Secaucus: Citadel Press.</li>

<li>Schopenhauer, A., <em>The World as Will and Representation</em>,
E. F. J. Payne (trans.), New York: Dover Publications, 1966.</li>

<li>Sidgwick, H., <em>Methods of Ethics</em>, 7th edn, Indianapolis:
Hackett, 1981.</li>

<li>Spinoza, B., <em>Ethics</em>, G. H. R. Parkinson (trans.), Oxford:
Oxford University Press, 2000.</li>

<li>Stevenson, C., [1944] 1962, <em>Ethics and Language</em>, New
Haven: Yale University Press.</li>

<li>Suarez, Francisco, <em>De Legibus</em>, in <em>Selections from
Three Works of Francisco Suarez, S. J.</em>, 2 vols., Oxford:
Clarendon Press; and London: H. Milford, 1944.</li>

<li>Voltaire, <em>Letters of Voltaire and Frederick the Great</em>,
Richard Aldington (trans.), New York: Brentano&rsquo;s, 1927.</li>

<li>Wittgenstein, L., [1953] 1960, <em>Philosophical
Investigations</em>, G. E. M. Anscombe (trans.), New York:
Macmillan.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, [1921] 1961, <em>Tractatus
Logico-Philosophicus</em>, London: Routledge &amp; Kegan Paul.</li>
</ul>

